# Clean Architecture in .NET

![Sample Architecture](/images/sample.png)

Clean Architecture is a way of structuring your .NET applications for maintainability, testability, and scalability.

## Key Benefits

- **Testability**: Business logic separated from frameworks
- **Independence**: Change frameworks without affecting core logic
- **Maintainability**: Clear separation of concerns

## The Layers

### Domain Layer
Your business entities and rules. Framework-agnostic.

```csharp
public class User
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string Email { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; }
}
```

### Application Layer
Use cases and business logic orchestration.

```csharp
public class CreateUserUseCase
{
    private readonly IUserRepository _repository;

    public CreateUserUseCase(IUserRepository repository)
    {
        _repository = repository;
    }

    public async Task Execute(CreateUserRequest request)
    {
        var user = new User { Email = request.Email, Name = request.Name };
        await _repository.AddAsync(user);
    }
}
```

### Infrastructure Layer
Database, external APIs, file systems.

```csharp
public class UserRepository : IUserRepository
{
    private readonly ApplicationDbContext _context;

    public async Task AddAsync(User user)
    {
        _context.Users.Add(user);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

### Presentation Layer
Controllers, UI, API endpoints.

```csharp
[ApiController]
[Route("api/[controller]")]
public class UsersController : ControllerBase
{
    private readonly CreateUserUseCase _useCase;

    [HttpPost]
    public async Task<IActionResult> Create([FromBody] CreateUserRequest request)
    {
        await _useCase.Execute(request);
        return Ok("User created");
    }
}
```

## Real Example: Babblr

In Babblr, we used clean architecture with SignalR for real-time messaging:
- **Domain**: Message entity, conversation rules
- **Application**: CreateMessageUseCase, SendMessageUseCase
- **Infrastructure**: PostgreSQL via Entity Framework, SignalR hubs
- **Presentation**: API endpoints, SignalR event handlers

## Next Steps

Start small. Apply layers to your next feature and watch your codebase become more maintainable.
